# Trivy ignore file for CYO Adventure container image scanning.
#
# Scope: ONLY base-image (Debian trixie) OS-package CVEs that currently have NO
# fixed version available upstream. Every entry below was confirmed via
#   trivy image --scanners vuln --severity CRITICAL,HIGH <image>
# to report an empty "Fixed Version" with status "affected" or "fix_deferred".
#
# Policy (per CLAUDE.md "Unfixed CVEs"): these are not suppressions of fixable
# issues. They are unavoidable until Debian ships patched packages. Re-evaluate
# on each base-image bump; remove any entry once a fixed version lands, and let
# the patched package flow in via the runtime stage `apt-get upgrade`.
#
# Remediation already applied in the Dockerfile (so these do NOT need ignores):
#   - curl / libcurl4t64 / libssh2-1t64 CVEs: curl is no longer installed.
#   - openssl / libssl CVE-2026-45447: resolved by `apt-get upgrade`.
#   - Go stdlib / esbuild CVEs: frontend/node_modules excluded via .dockerignore.
#
# Last reviewed: 2026-07-14 (gawk block only; see each block's own "Confirmed
# via" comment below for when it was individually last re-verified against a
# live Trivy run).

# --- perl-base (Perl + bundled Archive::Tar / IO-Compress); no Debian fix yet ---
CVE-2026-42496
CVE-2026-8376
CVE-2026-42497
CVE-2026-48962
CVE-2026-9538

# --- libsqlite3-0 (SQLite < 3.53.2); no Debian fix yet ---
CVE-2026-11822
CVE-2026-11824

# --- ncurses family: libncursesw6, libtinfo6, ncurses-base, ncurses-bin; no Debian fix yet ---
CVE-2025-69720

# --- libuuid1 (util-linux source pkg; libblkid dos.c integer overflow); no Debian fix yet ---
# Confirmed via the PR #165 Container Security run (empty Fixed Version, status
# "affected"). Documented in docs/known-vulnerabilities.md; reassess 2026-09-06.
CVE-2026-53615

# --- gawk (1:5.2.1-2+b1; builtin.c integer overflows, io.c UAF, buffer overflow); no Debian fix yet ---
# Confirmed via the PR #256 (v0.4.0 release) Container Security run: all four
# report an empty Fixed Version with status "affected". Newly disclosed after
# the 2026-07-08 review, so they post-date the entries above. Documented in
# docs/known-vulnerabilities.md; reassess 2026-09-12.
CVE-2026-40468
CVE-2026-40469
CVE-2026-40467
CVE-2026-40553

# --- libexpat1, libexpat1-dev (2.7.1-2+dhi5); no Debian fix yet ---
# Confirmed via the PR #299 (Python 3.14 runtime upgrade) Container Security
# run against ghcr.io/byronwilliamscpa/dhi-python:3.14-debian13: all six report
# an empty Fixed Version with status "affected". The identical CVE set was
# independently found on dhi-python:3.12-debian13's Renovate-proposed digest
# refresh while investigating PR #296, confirming a mirror-wide Debian 13
# base-layer regression, not specific to either Python version. Documented in
# docs/known-vulnerabilities.md; reassess 2026-09-17.
CVE-2025-59375
CVE-2026-25210
CVE-2026-45186
CVE-2026-56131
CVE-2026-56407
CVE-2026-56408

# --- linux-libc-dev (6.12.95-1+dhi0); kernel UAPI headers only, no running
# kernel code in this image; no Debian fix yet ---
# Confirmed via the same PR #299 run: all 34 report an empty Fixed Version
# with status "affected". The 34 span unrelated kernel subsystems (GEM, f2fs,
# Bluetooth, ksmbd, wifi drivers, RDMA, ARM64 KVM, netfilter, TCP, ALSA...),
# consistent with linux-libc-dev's known false-positive pattern: it carries
# kernel UAPI headers used at compile time, not a running kernel binary.
# Documented in docs/known-vulnerabilities.md; reassess 2026-09-17.
